Pillers of OPP's

1. Encapsulation
2. Inheritance
3. Abstraction
4. Polymorphism

Encapsulation. When we are wrapping properties and methods in a single unit, it is called encapsulation.
Abstraction: Hiding the internal logic to the User.
Inheritance: Coping the behaviour/properties of other class.
Polymorphish: Many forms. function overloading, operator overloading